text: I don't care about how you interpret laws, and I don't care about how you think our government has changed over a couple hundred years. Snowden committed treason. He gave away sensitive state information. He did pretty much the one thing you have to do to be accused of treason, and now people are defending and trying to absolve him? The stuff he revealed to the public? WE ALREADY KNEW ABOUT IT, GENUISES. He just "confirmed" our solid suspicions. You know how many highly classified items Snowden gave to China, Russia, and every other one of our not-so-friendly neighbors? Most commonfolk don't know this, but Snowden caused the largest breach in our nation's security... in our nation's history. The recent Chinese hackings don't even compare to the magnitude of sensitive information this traitor let out. Not a single one of you can tell about how many lives may have been lost or compromised because this idiot thought he knew better. Think what you want, but if you believe this man doesn't belong in a US prison for life, you can take his place.

text: If this movie came out in the 1950s, the people involved would never be seen in Hollywood again, and for once that would be justified. Its makers and everyone else who sings Snowden's praises are paranoid opportunist bandwagoners who are exaggerating a situation that is not as bad as they pretend, simply because they want to appear righteous. Sadly, common sense does not seem to be a priority. Why does everyone forget that Snowden gave top-secret information (a lot of which had nothing to do with American surveillance programs) to one of America's worst enemies and possibly the biggest threat to peace today? Snowden betrayed his country when he gave the information to Russia and is the worst American traitor in recent memory. Just wait, Russia will be using this as propaganda to continue its war against Ukraine and the West, people might die because of this. Tell me, if Snowden was some sort of martyr for free speech, why did he flee to one of the most censored countries in the world?

text: Anyone else find it strange that Snowden is in Russia? He could have stayed in Hong Kong since China doesn't have an extradition treaty with the US. He could literally be in any country that the US doesn't have an extradition treaty with and he chose Russia of all places. Russia, America's rival since the Cold War. I get that he gets FSB protection but it seems too convenient. Ever since I watched the movie Eagle Eye in 2008, I suspected that the government could be monitoring everyone's phones, internet usage and e.t.c. I was merely surprised that it was confirmed by Snowden. He is just one man, how could he have possibly gotten the files out without some help? He may deny being a Russian agent, but I do not believe he was able to do all this on his own. Perhaps the Chinese got involved at first and then wouldn't support him so he fled to Russia

text: Dude was a data analyst, computer nerd, math geek, Knight of Transparency & Liberty. Every life has a boring layer & an epic/bigger purpose layer.  I'm lovin' that this movie is coming out!  Harry spent years practicing how to transfigure cups.  Aragorn spent most of his time walking through the woods, and trying to get some calories.  Snowden mostly sat behind a computer, typing.  Both layers - at the same time! Boring/Epic.  I think we all have those two layers. It's easy for us to get caught up in the boring or mundane - but what's the REAL story?
